Key Match Events: Quincy Olivari stood out with his relentless energy, strong defense, rebounding, and impressive 3-point shooting in the Lakers' 107-102 win against the Milwaukee Bucks.
Olivari hit crucial shots and showcased his relentless full-court defense and hustle, making a significant impact on both ends of the floor.
In just 9 minutes and 24 seconds of play, Quincy Olivari scored 11 points on 4-of-6 shooting, including 3-of-6 from 3-point range, grabbed five rebounds, and handed out two assists.
LeBron James contributed 11 points, six rebounds, and four assists in 16 minutes of action.
Anthony Davis added 11 points, eight rebounds, and three blocks in his 25 minutes of play.
Rui Hachimura put up 14 points and collected five rebounds.
Dalton Knecht chipped in with 13 points and eight rebounds.
Gabe Vincent scored eight points on efficient 3-of-5 shooting.
The Lakers put together a 9-2 scoring run to even the game after Milwaukee rested Giannis Antetokounmpo and Damian Lillard.
The Lakers' bench fought back from a 15-point deficit, with Quincy Olivari and Maxwell Lewis knocking down 3-pointers to regain the lead.
The Lakers' scoring spree reached 20 unanswered points before the Bucks broke the drought.
Post-Match Reflections: JJ Redick praised Quincy Olivari for his exceptional effort and game-changing performance.
LeBron James praised Quincy Olivari for his game-changing performance and acknowledged how the young guard made the most of his opportunity.
